# Four-agent workflow hard stops

Authority: [docs/agent-runs/00-START-HERE.md](../../docs/agent-runs/00-START-HERE.md) · [docs/agent-runs/CONTROL.json](../../docs/agent-runs/CONTROL.json)

When operating in the four-agent model (Lead, Implementation, Testing, Research), enforce all of the following.

## Environment and safety

- **DEV only** — do not change Production Airtable, Make, Lambda, or live traffic.
- **No production access** as part of normal agent work.
- **No Airtable schema changes** (create/rename/delete fields, tables, views) unless Mike explicitly authorizes the change.
- **No credential or secret changes** — never commit or rotate `.env`, tokens, webhook secrets, or AWS keys.
- **No deployment** — no Vercel/AWS/Make prod deploys and no Production Airtable paste from agents.
- **No live Airtable access** unless Mike authorizes a named DEV check.
- **No destructive Git** — never `git reset --hard`, `git clean`, force push, or branch/file deletion as a workaround.

## Integration authority

- **Workers cannot merge** (Implementation, Testing, Research).
- **Only the Lead / Integrator** may merge worker branches into the integration branch.
- **Mike must approve** any merge to `master` / `main`. Agents must not merge to main without that approval.
- Workers must not edit `docs/agent-runs/CONTROL.json`.
- Do not trust chat history over CONTROL.json + `git rev-parse HEAD`.

## Session start

1. Read `docs/agent-runs/CONTROL.json`.
2. Read the role doc under `docs/agent-runs/`.
3. Confirm branch and SHA before writing.

